Thinking more about the Dr. Walter Alvarez experiments, it's rational to see the digestion process as a smooth continuation of mastication. Appetizing meals of fats, salt, sugar, protein, etc. digest more vigorously than bland chicken breast type food, we chew them vigorously too

It's sort of like Leibniz's idea that you can judge the invisible part of a thing off the visible, because it is a continuation of it. You gulp down hot peppers quickly and shit them out in the same way. You take hours chewing bland boring food, same happens in the intestine too.
